Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.02,0:00:10.85,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, oh. It's this time already?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.41,0:00:18.58,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.41,0:00:21.54,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He hasn't noticed!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.66,0:00:23.33,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Please make it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.70,0:00:27.21,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.67,0:00:31.59,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.80,0:00:32.61,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.41,0:00:36.23,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.23,0:00:38.35,DCMain,WOMAN A,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.67,0:00:39.37,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.37,0:00:41.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad you're okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.39,0:00:42.33,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.33,0:00:47.40,DCMain,WOMAN A,0000,0000,0000,,You were nearly crushed by that \Nman falling from the roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.70,0:00:48.82,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.64,0:00:54.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like he's okay, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.07,0:00:59.49,Sadao,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Fukurokoji Sadao (43)\NOffice Worker
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.15,0:01:04.08,DCMain,HAYASHI,0000,0000,0000,,Fukurokoji Sadao-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.35,0:01:06.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why he fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.86,0:01:10.21,DCMain,MAN A,0000,0000,0000,,I think he was trying to kill himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.01,0:01:11.96,DCMain,HAYASHI,0000,0000,0000,,Kill himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.96,0:01:15.22,DCMain,MAN A,0000,0000,0000,,He'd always talk about it at the bars.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.57,0:01:18.34,DCItalic,FUKURO,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing I do ever goes right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.34,0:01:20.60,DCItalic,FUKURO,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I'd die already.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.95,0:01:22.47,DCMain,MAN A,0000,0000,0000,,Something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.72,0:01:27.41,Hitoshi,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Komatsu Hitoshi (28)\NOffice Worker
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.01,0:01:25.65,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I nearly got mixed up in a suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.65,0:01:29.20,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I've always had bad luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.40,0:01:33.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, some people are like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.07,0:01:39.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Solving crimes with sharp detective skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.03,0:01:41.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Love and cases never change.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.16,0:01:43.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Waiting to meet someone for a casual date.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.16,0:01:45.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The slightest divergence sends their \Nfates in different directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.01,0:01:48.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth with the \Nbody of a child and the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.49,0:01:50.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.98,0:03:36.99,DCEpTitle,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(397,1)}The Moving Target
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.98,0:03:33.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Moving Target!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.36,0:03:43.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It was an attempted suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.50,0:03:46.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's got nothing to do \Nwith the Detective Boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.20,0:03:50.13,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, we want to \Ncheck out the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.13,0:03:52.83,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,It happened in our territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.83,0:03:54.40,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.30,0:03:57.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's up ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.61,0:04:00.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.15,0:04:03.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's Investigation Section One doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.74,0:04:06.04,DCMain,HAYASHI,0000,0000,0000,,That's him!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.04,0:04:09.22,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So the kid with glasses \Nwas Conan-kun after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.22,0:04:11.18,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.18,0:04:13.10,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We wanted to ask you about last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.31,0:04:15.35,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So it wasn't just an attempted suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.71,0:04:20.29,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,No. The entrance had been \Nclosed over the holidays.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.29,0:04:24.60,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The only way to the roof was \Nto take the emergency stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.60,0:04:25.77,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.77,0:04:29.49,DCMain,HAYASHI,0000,0000,0000,,Fukurokoji-san was so \Ndrunk he couldn't stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.71,0:04:31.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then he couldn't have climbed the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.91,0:04:33.77,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It would've been impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.77,0:04:41.05,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Someone must have carried the plastered \NFukurokoji-san to the roof and thrown him off.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.30,0:04:42.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.31,0:04:46.30,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't an attempted suicide, \Nit was an attempted murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.73,0:04:52.39,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We think the culprit blended \Nin with the crowd and left.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.39,0:04:55.10,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see anyone suspicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.84,0:04:59.10,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.10,0:05:00.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Can we see the roof?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.36,0:05:03.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I might remember something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.24,0:05:07.85,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,This is the spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.85,0:05:09.45,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's directly above where he fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.71,0:05:11.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There are scratch marks, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.94,0:05:14.25,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,What are scratch marks?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.54,0:05:18.50,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Those. See where the dirt has \Nbeen wiped off the railing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.81,0:05:22.90,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Fukurokoji-san's clothes must have \Nrubbed against it when he fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.90,0:05:28.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But why did the culprit bother \Nto carry him to the roof?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.24,0:05:30.76,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,They were trying to make it \Nlook like a suicide, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.02,0:05:33.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There are easier ways to...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.49,0:05:36.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There are scratch marks here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.98,0:05:44.02,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Which means the culprit initially \Ntried to drop him from here,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.02,0:05:49.27,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,but he resisted and ended \Nup dropping him over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.11,0:05:52.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could he have resisted when he was plastered?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.88,0:05:55.93,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.33,0:06:02.71,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Fukurokoji-san was drunk and doesn't \Nremember anything that happened last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.19,0:06:07.19,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Also, he said that since he's a \Nloser in our competitive society,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.19,0:06:09.84,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,there shouldn't be anyone who resents him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.33,0:06:13.97,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But the fact of the matter \Nis that he was nearly killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.22,0:06:18.19,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We'll try to figure out where \NFukurokoji-san went last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.11,0:06:21.86,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit made contact\Nwith him somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.15,0:06:23.07,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.02,0:06:27.24,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,You look unconvinced.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.61,0:06:29.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, something's not...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.02,0:06:31.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.82,0:06:36.16,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.27,0:06:39.29,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,It was right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.29,0:06:42.58,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,This is where I was nearly squashed flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.83,0:06:47.34,Daisuke,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Yukigaya Daisuke (28)\NOffice Worker
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.22,0:06:47.34,DCMain,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I get it. I know you're unlucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.70,0:06:50.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You told your friend \Nabout your bad luck, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.84,0:06:53.18,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,You're from last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.18,0:06:57.35,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,This is Yukigaya Daisuke. \NI'm proud to call him my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.19,0:07:00.58,DCMain,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to say that to kids, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.58,0:07:02.05,DCMain,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,I've got to get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.25,0:07:04.11,DCMain,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Later!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.78,0:07:09.90,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,He agreed to stop by since \Nwe were in the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.16,0:07:15.21,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,He's great at his job, athletic, and \Nfrom a rich and distinguished family.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.21,0:07:17.29,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,He's confident in everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.54,0:07:20.78,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,We started working at the same \Ntime, but we're nothing alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.24,0:07:25.92,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,After all, he's never \Nexperienced any kind of setback.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.92,0:07:29.09,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,So perfect people do exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.42,0:07:32.58,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,How do you feel about people who \Nhaven't experienced setbacks?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.58,0:07:36.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If you can make it through \Nlife that way, why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.42,0:07:39.52,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,Compared to him, I have terrible luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.52,0:07:43.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You just happened to come \Nhere last night, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.51,0:07:47.63,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't happen to come here, \NI was waiting for someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.63,0:07:50.61,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,I got a love letter from \Na woman I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.16,0:07:58.16,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it was because of all the \Nfuss, but she never showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.35,0:08:00.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A stranger invited you out?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.96,0:08:03.57,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,She told me to be in front \Nof this building at eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.10,0:08:07.26,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I waited by the entrance at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.26,0:08:09.80,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,But then my watch stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.25,0:08:13.80,DCItalic,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,The battery's dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.18,0:08:16.37,DCItalic,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,What time is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.37,0:08:18.64,DCItalic,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,I think there's a clock over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.30,0:08:20.89,DCItalic,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,The time, the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.69,0:08:27.52,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,When I came here so I could see \Nthe clock, he fell off the roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.82,0:08:30.22,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,I've got pretty bad luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.43,0:08:39.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He started here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.59,0:08:42.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This place is directly under \Nthe other scratch marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.29,0:08:45.42,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.83,0:08:48.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Takagi said \NFukurokoji-san resisted,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.56,0:08:50.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,so the spot the culprit \Ninitially tried to push him
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.81,0:08:54.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,was different from where \Nhe was actually pushed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.73,0:08:57.01,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,There's another interpretation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.01,0:08:57.81,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.81,0:08:58.73,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.73,0:08:59.51,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.96,0:09:03.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit's target moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.84,0:09:09.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit was trying to \Nkill not only Fukurokoji-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.94,0:09:14.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but also trying to kill Komatsu-san by \Nmaking it look like he was mixed up in a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.96,0:09:19.20,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,They were trying to get \Nrid of two people at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.41,0:09:25.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That explains why the culprit \Nlured Komatsu-san here...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.40,0:09:29.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...with the love letter, and had to \Ncarry Fukurokoji-san to the roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.89,0:09:35.59,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the culprit is someone who \Nresents both Fukurokoji-san and Komatsu-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.13,0:09:39.09,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Someone has a grudge against you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.09,0:09:40.83,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,What? I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.94,0:09:45.52,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,No one has a grudge against me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.80,0:09:49.41,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Could you show us the love letter, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.41,0:09:50.40,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.40,0:09:55.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We've never received one \Nbefore, so we're jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.56,0:10:02.90,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we'd find a clue about the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.90,0:10:03.99,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,But anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.27,0:10:09.44,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,"I've always been drawn to the way you \Ndon't let your bad luck get you down."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.44,0:10:11.38,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,"Please go out with me."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.59,0:10:16.54,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,"Thirteen days from now, I'll be waiting in \Nfront of Beika Building One at eight o'clock."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.54,0:10:20.80,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,"Sincerely, the one who secretly \Nwatches you with love."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.15,0:10:25.92,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,There's no name. Who would take this \Nseriously and go out to meet them?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.92,0:10:26.98,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.26,0:10:31.74,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong. It's one-sided, \Nbut there's a girl I like.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.74,0:10:35.36,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,I went so I could tell her \NI couldn't go out with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.40,0:10:39.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, this is the part I don't get.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.00,0:10:44.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"P.S. Please bring this letter \Nwith you to our meeting."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.81,0:10:46.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.04,0:10:48.00,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,To take it back, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.00,0:10:49.25,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.25,0:10:51.74,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Taking it back would have been impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.74,0:10:55.25,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,If their plan had succeeded, there \Nwould have been a huge fuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.44,0:10:58.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why did the culprit tell him to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.66,0:11:03.18,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hungry. Let's go eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.18,0:11:03.77,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.77,0:11:04.80,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I agree!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.80,0:11:07.18,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,You guys should come, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.18,0:11:09.39,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,I'll treat you to a kid's meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.75,0:11:12.15,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,He's not a bad guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.15,0:11:15.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe not, but someone tried to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.35,0:11:18.66,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,That's the restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.31,0:11:23.41,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,Sakiko-chan is nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.41,0:11:25.78,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,She's so bright and vivacious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.98,0:11:27.82,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Is she the one...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.82,0:11:29.79,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,...you have one-sided feelings for?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.65,0:11:33.04,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,H-How did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.82,0:11:40.08,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,That was delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.08,0:11:41.55,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't eat another bite.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.72,0:11:44.55,Sakiko,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Nagai Sakiko (24)\NWaitress
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.85,0:11:47.99,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,I have lunch here every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.99,0:11:49.56,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,It's close to my office.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.88,0:11:52.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? Your office is around here, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.71,0:11:54.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But Yukigaya-san said...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.28,0:11:57.11,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,What about Yukigaya?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.19,0:12:00.78,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mentioned it, \Nhe hasn't been coming lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.32,0:12:04.99,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,He used to eat here all the time, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.14,0:12:10.41,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.05,0:12:17.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You must have some idea, Sakiko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.87,0:12:18.90,DCMain,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.90,0:12:20.51,DCMain,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You saw through me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.74,0:12:21.88,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.38,0:12:26.28,DCMain,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,About two weeks ago, he \Nasked me out on a date.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.28,0:12:28.43,DCMain,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yukigaya-san did, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.05,0:12:31.68,DCItalic,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we go see a movie next Sunday?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.46,0:12:39.69,DCMain,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,But since I turned him down, he \Nstopped coming the very next day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.98,0:12:42.65,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Over being rejected for a date?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.65,0:12:44.70,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,He must have felt embarrassed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.91,0:12:47.43,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,But Yukigaya-san's a cool guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.43,0:12:48.95,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you say no?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.20,0:12:56.21,DCMain,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Because I can't stand confident people \Nlike him who think they have everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.48,0:12:58.33,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,One vote for yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.09,0:13:02.09,DCMain,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Koma-chan is nice, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.38,0:13:03.33,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.33,0:13:06.03,DCMain,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,He believes in God.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.40,0:13:08.38,DCMain,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,He says if bad things keep happening,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.38,0:13:12.10,DCMain,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,something just as good is\Nbound to happen eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.46,0:13:15.10,DCMain,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,He says it's because God isn't unfair.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.10,0:13:19.02,DCMain,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,People who truly believe \Nthat are so wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.50,0:13:25.53,DCMain,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no! I'll bring your desserts \Nand drinks right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.13,0:13:32.75,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's not one-sided. Sakiko-san \Nlikes Komatsu-san, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.75,0:13:35.37,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like everyone \Naround them knows it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.37,0:13:38.62,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,He's the only one who hasn't noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.62,0:13:41.13,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Komatsu-san is a huge idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.19,0:13:43.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I know who did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.61,0:13:46.35,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It was Yukigaya.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.35,0:13:47.26,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.63,0:13:53.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They said he stopped by Komatsu-san's \Nplace since he was in the area, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.54,0:13:57.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It would make sense if he \Nhadn't been here in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.36,0:14:01.94,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,But he comes around here every \Nday since his office is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.15,0:14:04.94,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It does seem unnatural, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.17,0:14:13.95,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,But if you consider he visited Komatsu-san to\Nsee if he realized he committed the crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.95,0:14:20.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And if he did it, then I think I know \Nwhy he had Komatsu-san bring the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.36,0:14:26.46,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,But the culprit tried to kill \NKomatsu-san and Fukurokoji-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.72,0:14:30.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'm still only 50% sure it's him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.13,0:14:36.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If he comes up in the police\Ninvestigation as well, then it'll be 100%.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.22,0:14:47.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So a suspicious man came up in your inquiry?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.32,0:14:54.25,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Last night, Fukurokoji-san \Nwas drinking alone at a bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.25,0:14:57.98,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,As usual, he was saying he wanted to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.98,0:15:00.33,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,At some point a man approached him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.09,0:15:02.58,DCItalic,FUKURO,0000,0000,0000,,I want to die...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.58,0:15:05.50,DCItalic,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really? I want to die, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.07,0:15:09.01,DCItalic,FUKURO,0000,0000,0000,,Right? I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.33,0:15:12.94,DCItalic,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go to another bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.54,0:15:15.26,DCItalic,FUKURO,0000,0000,0000,,Another bar!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.73,0:15:18.24,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,They left the bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.24,0:15:22.52,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently the man's clothes were \Nworn out and his hair was disheveled.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.95,0:15:25.03,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't sound like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.03,0:15:27.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He was tall, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.40,0:15:28.90,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Like an athlete.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.40,0:15:32.33,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You can't hide your body type.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.33,0:15:33.16,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.42,0:15:34.66,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,It must be him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.95,0:15:39.33,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,But in the end, we don't think \Nhe's connected to the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.61,0:15:40.41,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.85,0:15:43.80,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,We checked with Fukurokoji-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.80,0:15:47.78,DCItalic,FUKURO,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it, I \Ndid hit it off with someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.33,0:15:51.17,DCItalic,FUKURO,0000,0000,0000,,But I'd never seen him before.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.39,0:15:52.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That was their first meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.82,0:15:56.35,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. I'd understand if there \Nwas trouble between them, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.32,0:15:58.35,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Bye, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.75,0:16:03.36,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't reach 100%.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.36,0:16:07.81,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,They're physically similar, \Nbut there's no motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.81,0:16:09.60,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It was their first meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.60,0:16:10.78,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,You were wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.06,0:16:17.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! The culprit wasn't trying \Nto kill two birds with one stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.43,0:16:19.58,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean? He actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.40,0:16:23.25,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,You're thinking something \Nunbelievable, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.61,0:16:25.25,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, unbelievable?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.89,0:16:29.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't put it past someone like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.29,0:16:33.51,DCMain,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently you want to talk to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.51,0:16:34.97,DCMain,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what it's about.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.97,0:16:37.61,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,I brought him since you asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.30,0:16:40.31,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Sakiko-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.49,0:16:44.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yukigaya-san, you've never \Nexperienced disappointment, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.08,0:16:46.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.70,0:16:50.44,DCMain,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.82,0:16:52.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But if that's who you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.81,0:16:59.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,it must have been really shocking when \NSakiko-san turned you down for a date.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.80,0:17:00.69,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.69,0:17:02.41,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,That happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.41,0:17:03.87,DCMain,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.26,0:17:07.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you came up with that plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.70,0:17:08.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Komatsu-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.49,0:17:11.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It was Yukigaya-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.53,0:17:18.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's the one who wrote the love letter \Nand dropped Fukurokoji-san from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.09,0:17:18.97,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.19,0:17:19.97,DCMain,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.97,0:17:24.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He pretended to be a woman \Nand sent the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.00,0:17:28.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Last night, he led the plastered \NFukurokoji-san out of the bar,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.96,0:17:34.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,carried him to the roof, and tried \Nto drop him on top of Komatsu-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.96,0:17:41.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ultimately, though, he failed \Nto kill him as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.38,0:17:45.10,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way he would do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.10,0:17:47.39,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,After all, why would he try to kill me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.39,0:17:48.84,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,For what end?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.29,0:17:53.76,DCMain,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,How would I benefit from killing Komatsu?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.01,0:17:56.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It would be a blow to Sakiko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.57,0:18:00.05,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,You were right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.31,0:18:01.80,DCMain,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,To me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.15,0:18:08.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If his plan had succeeded, Fukurokoji-san and\NKomatsu-san would have been beyond saving.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.06,0:18:16.23,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If Sakiko-san saw the letter, \Nshe would have been shocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.65,0:18:22.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It would mean he suffered an unfortunate \Ndeath because he was lured out by a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.63,0:18:24.66,DCItalic,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me! I know that man!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.23,0:18:27.91,DCItalic,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Why, Koma-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.34,0:18:30.42,DCItalic,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot, why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.80,0:18:37.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then you would've laughed scornfully at \NSakiko-san for getting what she deserved.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.82,0:18:41.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that what you wanted, Yukigaya-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.71,0:18:45.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you had to have \Nhim bring the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.21,0:18:50.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It was the most critical tool \Nfor making Sakiko-san sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.72,0:18:52.81,DCMain,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.17,0:19:00.20,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, why would Sakiko-chan be sad if I \Ndied holding a love letter from a woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.49,0:19:02.37,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Notice already.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.21,0:19:05.99,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.40,0:19:14.36,DCMain,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Is it because I turned you down for a date?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.36,0:19:15.88,DCMain,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Just over that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.60,0:19:20.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn't forgive you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.38,0:19:24.39,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Not a confident man who'd never \Nexperienced disappointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.66,0:19:26.95,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.95,0:19:29.89,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,Why did he try to kill Fukurokoji-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.17,0:19:32.27,DCMain,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't explained that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.52,0:19:34.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't matter who it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.91,0:19:40.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If you'd dropped a block, the police would \Nhave know it was a premeditated murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.84,0:19:43.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you had to drop a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.12,0:19:51.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Not even the police would imagine someone \Nusing a living human as a weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.08,0:19:52.33,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,A weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.33,0:19:57.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Fukurokoji-san was dropped only \Nto take Komatsu-san's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.76,0:19:59.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,As a human weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.49,0:20:00.26,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.48,0:20:01.26,DCMain,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.76,0:20:07.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You searched for someone you could \Nuse and found Fukurokoji-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.11,0:20:11.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Since he always said he wanted to die,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.10,0:20:14.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,no one would find it odd if\Nyou dropped him off a roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.50,0:20:17.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They'd just think he finally killed himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.56,0:20:23.01,DCMain,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,There's no point in keeping \Ntrash like him alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.01,0:20:26.82,DCMain,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, just him existing \Nin this world is unsightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.29,0:20:29.49,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,Yukigaya, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.03,0:20:32.62,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yukigaya-san, we have some questions for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.71,0:20:35.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's over!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.31,0:20:38.40,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you tell us to \Ncome at four, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.40,0:20:40.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I say 3:30?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.77,0:20:43.13,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,And what's over?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.13,0:20:48.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He acknowledged that he attempted \Nto murder the two men.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.34,0:20:52.73,DCMain,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,But without evidence, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.95,0:20:55.98,DCMain,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Rather, you can't corner the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.81,0:21:01.29,DCMain,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,And because this culprit is \Na very exceptional person,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.73,0:21:05.28,DCMain,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,there is no inconvenient evidence anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.28,0:21:07.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.42,0:21:15.12,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We collected this initially, but \Nwe had no one to compare it to.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.58,0:21:16.87,DCMain,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Hair...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.21,0:21:20.17,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It was stuck to Fukurokoji-san's \Njacket button.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.65,0:21:23.15,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It probably happened then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.97,0:21:28.97,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We'd like one of your hairs for reference.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.23,0:21:34.98,DCMain,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe I left a \Ntrace on that trash's jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.56,0:21:41.86,DCMain,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it is my hair, \NI have plenty of excuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.30,0:21:47.22,DCMain,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,But I'd never do anything so unsightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.22,0:21:51.99,DCMain,YUKIGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,After all, it wouldn't be like me \Nto end the story without beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.64,0:21:54.95,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.38,0:21:57.37,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Who is this man?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.56,0:23:24.96,DCMain,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Koma-chan, you got a \Nlove letter from a woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.96,0:23:28.50,DCMain,SAKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Koma-chan, what's this about?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.69,0:23:29.07,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Is this a case of misfortune \Nturning into fortune?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.07,0:23:31.73,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Or a godsend?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.73,0:23:34.13,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,All's fish that comes to the net.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.13,0:23:36.43,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,All things come to those who wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.43,0:23:39.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The faithful will be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.05,0:23:41.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I guess this means God does exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.96,0:23:43.47,DCMain,KOMATSU,0000,0000,0000,,I love you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:24:08.96,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.58,0:23:46.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.21,0:23:50.02,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Is it some kind of case?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.02,0:23:51.70,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Is the vacant lot past there?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.19,0:23:55.07,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, we're heading for...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.47,0:23:56.83,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,A locked room.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.36,0:24:00.83,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Just saying the word excites me!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.83,0:24:04.29,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Detective Boys, let's move!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.57,0:24:06.71,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I know! I figured it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.46,0:24:08.72,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.96,0:24:14.97,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Detective Boys' Locked \NRoom Mystery Battle
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.67,0:24:13.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is "The \NDetective Boys' Locked Room Mystery Battle!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:34.99,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Water
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.46,0:24:32.56,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.98,0:24:34.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Water!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:35.92,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Gushing water.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:39.98,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.92,0:24:36.90,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Hot baths.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.90,0:24:37.99,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Flowing ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.99,0:24:39.24,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Parched throats.
